Convert 10 sign magnitude representations to decimal numbers 
The two's complement binary representation is restricted to 8 bits (1 bit for sign 7  bits value) for simplicity.
Give decimal equivalent of the following sign magnitude representations (maximum eight bits)
decimal equivalent of 01111111
127

decimal equivalent of 10000000
-128 

decimal equivalent of 00000000
0 

decimal equivalent of 11111111
-1 

decimal equivalent of 01010101
85 

decimal equivalent of 10101010
-86 

decimal equivalent of 01100110
102 

decimal equivalent of 10011001
-101 

decimal equivalent of 00110011
99 

decimal equivalent of 11001100
-57 
